The paper discusses a method for steganography, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The method uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) to generate secret messages without modifying the cover image, which involves image processing and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of GANs also involves machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a data-hiding key, which is a common technique in multimedia security (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves meeting Kerckhoffs' principle, which is a fundamental principle in cryptography and security (cs.AI).
